<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,152,711]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,351,607,633]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">Remarks:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ahti &amp; Sipman" authorityYear="2013" box="[351,537,608,633]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Cladoniaceae" genus="Cladonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="recta">
<emphasis box="[351,537,608,633]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">Cladonia recta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles most 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller Argoviensis" authorityYear="1880" baseAuthorityName="Nylander" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[766,925,608,633]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Cladoniaceae" genus="Cladonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="peltastica">
<emphasis box="[766,925,608,633]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">C. peltastica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but is much more slender and forms conspicuous, straight, erect colonies. However, it is possible that it represents an usnic acid-free chemotype of that species.
</paragraph>
